class="card-collection-flat"><a class="card-collection-flat__title-link" href="/features/"><h2 class="card-collection-flat__title-header card-collection-flat__title">Featured</h2></a><div class="ccf-container ccf-container--section-top-grid"><ul class="featured-articles-list"><li class="featured-articles-list__item"><article class="gc u-clickable-card gc--type-post gc--with-image"><div class="gc__image-placeholder"></div><div class="gc__content"><div class="gc__header-wrap"><div class="gc__header-meta u-clickable-card__exclude"></div><h3 class="gc__title"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" href="/features/2026/5/1/on-may-day-gazas-workers-find-whatever-source-of-income-they-can"><span>On May Day, Gaza’s workers find whatever source of income they can</span></a></h3></div><div class="gc__body-wrap"><div class="gc__excerpt"><p>Gaza’s economic collapse leaves workers in perilous jobs, with unemployment soaring amid ongoing devastation.</p></div></div><footer class="gc__footer"><div class="gc__meta"><div class="gc__date gc__date--published"><div class="gc__date__date"><div class="date-simple"><span class="screen-reader-text">Published On 1 May 2026</span><span aria-hidden="true">1 May 2026</span></div></div></div></div></footer></div><div class="gc__image-wrap u-clickable-card__exclude"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" tabindex="-1" aria-label="ibrahim stands before a pile of rubble" href="/features/2026/5/1/on-may-day-gazas-workers-find-whatever-source-of-income-they-can"><div class="article-card__image-wrap article-card__featured-image" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="false" data-testid="card-media-preview"><div class="responsive-image"><img class="article-card__image gc__image" loading="eager" src="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/873A9713-1777576366.jpg?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80" srcSet="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/873A9713-1777576366.jpg?resize=120%2C80&amp;quality=80 120w, /wp-content/uploads/2026/04/873A9713-1777576366.jpg?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80 270w" sizes="(max-width: 120px) 120px, (max-width: 270px) 270px, 270px" alt="Ibrahim stands before a pile of rubble"/></div></div></a></div></article></li><li class="featured-articles-list__item"><article class="gc u-clickable-card gc--type-post gc--with-image"><div class="gc__image-placeholder"></div><div class="gc__content"><div class="gc__header-wrap"><div class="gc__header-meta u-clickable-card__exclude"></div><h3 class="gc__title"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" href="/news/2026/4/30/its-all-very-toxic"><span>‘Environmental disaster’: Ukrainian attacks on oil refineries rock Russia</span></a></h3></div><div class="gc__body-wrap"><div class="gc__excerpt"><p>Ukrainian forces have hammered one of Russia’s largest sites in Tuapse, causing oil spills and black rain.</p></div></div><footer class="gc__footer"><div class="gc__meta"><div class="gc__date gc__date--published"><div class="gc__date__date"><div class="date-simple"><span class="screen-reader-text">Published On 30 Apr 2026</span><span aria-hidden="true">30 Apr 2026</span></div></div></div></div></footer></div><div class="gc__image-wrap u-clickable-card__exclude"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" tabindex="-1" aria-label="officials walk along a street during a visit by krasnodar region&#x27;s governor in tuapse, russia" href="/news/2026/4/30/its-all-very-toxic"><div class="article-card__image-wrap article-card__featured-image" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="false" data-testid="card-media-preview"><div class="responsive-image"><img class="article-card__image gc__image" loading="eager" src="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2026-04-28T141859Z_991775446_RC2EYKAT07FU_RTRMADP_3_UKRAINE-CRISIS-REFINERY-FIRE-1777477892.jpg?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80" srcSet="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2026-04-28T141859Z_991775446_RC2EYKAT07FU_RTRMADP_3_UKRAINE-CRISIS-REFINERY-FIRE-1777477892.jpg?resize=120%2C80&amp;quality=80 120w, /wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2026-04-28T141859Z_991775446_RC2EYKAT07FU_RTRMADP_3_UKRAINE-CRISIS-REFINERY-FIRE-1777477892.jpg?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80 270w" sizes="(max-width: 120px) 120px, (max-width: 270px) 270px, 270px" alt="Officials walk along a street during a visit by Krasnodar region&#x27;s governor in Tuapse, Russia"/></div></div></a></div></article></li><li class="featured-articles-list__item"><article class="gc u-clickable-card gc--type-post gc--with-image"><div class="gc__image-placeholder"></div><div class="gc__content"><div class="gc__header-wrap"><div class="gc__header-meta u-clickable-card__exclude"><div class="post-label"><span class="post-label__text">EXPLAINER</span></div></div><h3 class="gc__title"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" href="/features/2026/4/30/why-is-india-turning-to-crocodiles-and-snakes-to-fence-bangladesh-border"><span>Why is India turning to crocodiles and snakes to ‘fence’ Bangladesh border?</span></a></h3></div><div class="gc__body-wrap"><div class="gc__excerpt"><p>India wants to  the border with Bangladesh badly — even if it takes venomous snakes or crocodiles.</p></div></div><footer class="gc__footer"><div class="gc__meta"><div class="gc__date gc__date--published"><div class="gc__date__date"><div class="date-simple"><span class="screen-reader-text">Published On 30 Apr 2026</span><span aria-hidden="true">30 Apr 2026</span></div></div></div></div></footer></div><div class="gc__image-wrap u-clickable-card__exclude"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" tabindex="-1" aria-label="india" href="/features/2026/4/30/why-is-india-turning-to-crocodiles-and-snakes-to-fence-bangladesh-border"><div class="article-card__image-wrap article-card__featured-image" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="false" data-testid="card-media-preview"><div class="responsive-image"><img class="article-card__image gc__image" loading="eager" src="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2024-05-30T100339Z_1731458408_RC2ER7AG7XAM_RTRMADP_3_INDIA-ELECTION-CLIMATE-1777459768.jpg?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80" srcSet="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2024-05-30T100339Z_1731458408_RC2ER7AG7XAM_RTRMADP_3_INDIA-ELECTION-CLIMATE-1777459768.jpg?resize=120%2C80&amp;quality=80 120w, /wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2024-05-30T100339Z_1731458408_RC2ER7AG7XAM_RTRMADP_3_INDIA-ELECTION-CLIMATE-1777459768.jpg?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80 270w" sizes="(max-width: 120px) 120px, (max-width: 270px) 270px, 270px" alt="India"/></div></div></a></div></article></li><li class="featured-articles-list__item"><article class="gc u-clickable-card gc--type-post gc--with-image"><div class="gc__image-placeholder"></div><div class="gc__content"><div class="gc__header-wrap"><div class="gc__header-meta u-clickable-card__exclude"><div class="post-label"><span class="post-label__text">EXPLAINER</span></div></div><h3 class="gc__title"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" href="/news/2026/4/29/five-charts-that-show-the-rise-of-global-militarisation"><span>Five charts that show the rise of global militarisation</span></a></h3></div><div class="gc__body-wrap"><div class="gc__excerpt"><p>As countries spend more on their militaries, what does that mean for spending on healthcare and education?</p></div></div><footer class="gc__footer"><div class="gc__meta"><div class="gc__date gc__date--published"><div class="gc__date__date"><div class="date-simple"><span class="screen-reader-text">Published On 29 Apr 2026</span><span aria-hidden="true">29 Apr 2026</span></div></div></div></div></footer></div><div class="gc__image-wrap u-clickable-card__exclude"><a class="u-clickable-card__link" tabindex="-1" aria-label="interactive - military spending global cover image-1777457357" href="/news/2026/4/29/five-charts-that-show-the-rise-of-global-militarisation"><div class="article-card__image-wrap article-card__featured-image" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="false" data-testid="card-media-preview"><div class="responsive-image"><img class="article-card__image gc__image" loading="eager" src="/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/INTERACTIVE-Military-spending-global-cover-image-1777457357.png?resize=270%2C180&amp;quality=80" srcSet="/wp-conte